"the clipboard object(s). These commands honor the scale ratio lock on the "
"Selector Tool controls bar (between W and H fields), so that when that lock is "
"pressed, the other dimension of the selected object is scaled in the same "
"proportion; otherwise the other dimension is unchanged. The commands containing "
"“Separately” work similarly to the above described commands, except that they "
"scale each selected object separately to make it match the size/width/height of "
"the clipboard object(s)."
msgstr ""
